This paper deals with privacy concerns related to genetic data, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of searchable encryption, which is a technique used in databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures to efficiently perform the relatedness test, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CY) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques to match genetic data, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
